data.name: Spicy Carrot and Lentil Delight
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant and hearty dish featuring roasted carrots and protein-packed lentils, spiced to perfection with ginger and a hint of chili.
detailedCookingInstructions: On a baking sheet, toss the diced carrots with olive oil, salt, and black pepper. Roast for 25-30 minutes until tender and caramelized.
In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add minced garlic and grated ginger, sauté until fragrant, about 2 minutes.
Add the red lentils, vegetable broth, ground cumin, and chili powder to the pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer. Cook for 20 minutes, or until lentils are soft.
Once the carrots are done roasting, add them to the lentil mixture. Stir in the coconut milk and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper if needed.
Let the soup simmer for an additional 5-10 minutes. Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro.
